# Use Case — Insurance Call Assistant

## Context
An insurance company wanted to assist advisors during live client calls.

---

## Objectives
- Transcribe live audio conversations
- Identify speakers (advisor vs client)
- Understand customer intent
- Suggest relevant responses in real time

---

## Technical pipeline

Audio  
→ Speech-to-Text  
→ Speaker identification  
→ NLP analysis  
→ LLM reasoning  
→ Advisor assistance

---

## Technologies involved
- Speech-to-text engines
- NLP & embeddings
- LLMs
- HuggingFace models
- GPU acceleration
- Agent-based orchestration

---

## Value
- Improved advisor efficiency
- Better customer experience
- Consistent and compliant responses
